-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/south-african-daybook-african-union-on-libya-minerals-datatec-nedbank.html
South Africa  will host a meeting of
the  African Union ’s committee on  Libya  to discuss developments
in the North African country, according to the presidency.  The AU hasn’t recognized the National Transitional Council
as the governing authority in Libya even though a number of
countries have broken ranks and accepted the NTC as the
government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
